.SH NAME
tty_buffer_set_limit \- change the tty buffer memory limit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tty_buffer_set_limit
.BI "(struct tty_port *port "  ","
.BI "int limit "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
tty port to change
.IP "limit" 12
memory limit to set

Change the tty buffer memory limit.
Must be called before the other tty buffer functions are used.
